ЁЯМК
Today 5th October is the great event for everyone which is "International Observe the Moon Night- 2019", on the other hand from today "Space Week" has started. Space Week occurs from 4th October to 10th October. Today we will able to see the first quarter of the moon. ЁЯМХЁЯОЙ
"What's the FIRST QUARTER of THE MOON?"
The First Quarter Moon is a primary Moon phase when we can see exactly half of the Moon's surface illuminated. If it is the left or right half, depends on where you are on Earth. ЁЯМУ
"What will the effect of the first quarter of the moon on Tides?"
The ocean tides on Earth are mostly generated by the MoonтАЩs gravitational pull. At First and Third Quarter, the Moon and Sun pull in different directions, producing the smallest difference between high and low tide, known as "Neaps or Neap tide." ЁЯМК
The largest tidal range is during around Full Moon and New Moon. During these Moon phases, the gravitational forces of the Moon and the Sun combine to pull the oceanтАЩs water in the same direction. These tides are known as "Spring tides or King tides." ЁЯМК
The other primary Moon phase symbols in calendars are:
ЁЯМС = New Moon
ЁЯМХ = Full Moon,
ЁЯМЧ = Third Quarter
Happy Observing! ЁЯША

(рзи) ржЗржжрж╛ржирж┐ржВ ржбрзЗржЩрзНржЧрзБрж░ ржкрзНрж░ржХрзЛржкрзЗрж░ ржХрж╛рж░ржгрзЗ ржмрж┐ржнрж┐ржирзНржи ржорж┐ржбрж┐рзЯрж╛рзЯ ржЕржгрзБржЪржХрзНрж░рж┐ржХрж╛рж░ ржкрзНрж░рж╕ржЩрзНржЧ
